title: Fetty Wap cancels tour dates
text:
Share Updated: 11:53 am 
Rapper Fetty Wap has pulled out of a number of concerts as he recovers from his motorcycle accident in New Jersey over the weekend. 
Wap broke his left leg in three places when he collided with a vehicle while reportedly trying to overtake a car, and he has now cancelled tour dates to focus on his recovery. 
He will no longer perform at radio station Power 95.3's concert in Orlando, Florida, on Saturday, his own gig in Washington, D.C. on Oct. 11 or BBC Radio's 1Xtra Live showcase in Leeds, England, on Oct. 17. 
A representative for the Radio 1Xtra event says, "Unfortunately Fetty Wap will not be able to perform at 1Xtra Live in Leeds following his recent accident, and we are really sorry for all the fans who were looking forward to seeing him perform live... Everyone at 1Xtra wishes him a speedy recovery." 
Two other concert appearances during that period, in Pennsylvania and Virginia, had not been cancelled as WENN went to press. Copyright WENN.com
